A N A C T
RELATING TO TOWNS AND CITIES -- ZONING ORDINANCES
Introduced By: Representatives Place, Santucci, Quattrocchi, Hopkins, and Nardone
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: House Municipal Government & Housing
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 45-24 of the General Laws entitled "Zoning Ordinances" is hereby
2 amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 45-24-37.1. Home-based businesses.
4 Notwithstanding any zoning or other municipal ordinance to the contrary, any individual
5 operating a home-based business which meets the criteria provided by the Internal Revenue Code
6 for a home office tax deduction, may operate without securing any approvals from their
7 municipality; provided, that the home-based business does not store chemicals, other hazardous
8 materials, or park heavy equipment on the premises, and not more than ten percent (10%) of the
9 premises are used for parking in connection with the operation of the home-based business.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
